The course covers the aspects of the daily running of a dental clinic as a business, from the establishment of the clinic to the creation of a patient safety system.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide an introduction to the knowledge and activities that are necessary for the establishment of a dental clinic as well as for the day-to-day running of the clinic, without which quality dental care is not possible. It will also help the future dental entrepreneur to orientate oneself in the legislation and requirements for clinics in Estonia.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course the student: 1. Knows the basics of good quality dental care. 2. Knows the principles of data protection and work safety, and understands the importance of their implementation. 3. Has an overview of the structure of the clinic's staff and the general organisation of the practice. 4. Understands the need for correct documentation. 5. Has the ability to set up a quality management system for the clinic. 6. Can prepare documents and instructions necessary for the everyday running of the clinic.
